Three teams of health workers have also been deployed at Victoria Hospital in the town of Quatre Bornes. Those vaccinated will get a second dose of the AstraZeneca/Oxford vaccine in about 20 days. Mauritius received 100 000 doses of vaccine from India on Friday. A batch of 240 000 doses of the Pfizer-BioNtech vaccine is expected to arrive in the country by February 15, according to the World Health Organisation (WHO) representative, Laurent Musango. The Pfizer, BioNtech vaccines were obtained through Covax, a global initiative led by the WHO to make sure vaccines are shared fairly among all nations, rich and poor. --BBC--